    <sharedRules>
        <rule name="Markerlight" id="6023-0d3c-bd2e-4e07" hidden="false">
            <description>During each Reinforcement phase, place a number of Markerlight tokens next to each unit equal to the number of "Markerlight“ shots they have. These Markerlight tokens can be assigned to enemy units that are targeted by the activated unit. Friendly units that are in range and line of sight of the target may assign their Markerlight tokens to it as well during the same activation. A unit’s own Markerlight tokens have to be used up first before it may make use of Markerlight tokens from a friendly unit. Can not be assigned if the unit is locked in melee combat.
Markerlight tokens can be spent to gain a number of benefits (see table).
# Token/Cost - Effect
1 - For each token removed, one Seeker missile equipped by the unit may automatically hit the target.
1 - Reduce the enemy Leadership by a cumulative 1 until the end of the battle round.
2 - Attacks gain the cumulative "Sunder(1)" ability.
2 - Reduce the to hit penalty for Defensive Fire by 1.
2 - Re-roll ranged to hit rolls of 1 .
3 - The target must pass a Leadership test or gain a Battleshock token.
3 - The target is hit by a Seeker missile (see Armory) from outside the battlefield. Vehicles are hit on the side the unit would normally be able to hit.
Example A unit that wants to re-roll ranged to hit rolls of 1 and reduce the cover bonus for the enemy by 1 must remove a total of 4 tokens from the target unit.
Each token can only be used for a single effect from the table and all unused tokens are discarded at the end of the battle round. A unit may not have more than 4 Markerlight tokens on it at the same time.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Supporting Fire" id="7dbf-a849-32a1-4f86" hidden="false">
            <description>If a friendly unit within 6" is the target of a charge and is using Defensive Fire, this unit may be activated in the same way to use Defensive fire at the charging enemy. Note that this is only doable with an unused order token and will use up that same token.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Accelerator" id="e3a2-5c79-1b76-4768" hidden="false">
            <description>Pulse Accelerator Drones increase the range of all pulse weapons in the unit by 6".</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Environmental scan" id="cae8-6a3b-89aa-4457" hidden="false">
            <description>Enemy units charging a unit with a Warscaper Drone have to make a dangerous terrain test after their charge.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Drone protocols" id="1e58-b16f-8bf5-413d" hidden="false">
            <description>Drones are ignored when determining the unit's most used Toughness and Defensive rules. They move as fast as the unit they are attached to. They are considered as being part of the model that controls them. Drones controlled by a Drone controller can not be removed as casualties.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Grav inhibitor" id="8a41-27ab-759e-4f87" hidden="false">
            <description>Grav Inhibitor Drones reduce enemy Charge movements that target the model or its attached unit by 2".</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Shielded" id="b3bd-57a3-8a30-4c89" hidden="false">
            <description>Shield Drones confer a 5+ invulnerability save to themselves and their attached units.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Shrouded" id="eebf-1ccb-c417-4c2d" hidden="false">
            <description>Stealth Drones confer the ability "Stealth" and "Use cover" to themselves and their attached units.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Crisis bodyguard" id="dfa0-9a52-1388-43ba" hidden="false">
            <description>The Commander may join a unit of Crisis Honor Guard.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Shas'el" id="8200-5947-e67f-4d53" hidden="false">
            <description>May be equipped with one additional weapon and SUPPORT SYSTEM each.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Failure is not an option" id="ead1-64b1-9c7a-4307" hidden="false">
            <description>Friendly units within 12" may use the Ethereal's Leadership value.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Serene unifier" id="ce52-f26c-7a6d-4c09" hidden="false">
            <description>The model can invoke 1 invocation per turn. An invocation is successfully invoked on a roll of 3+. It knows all the powers from the list of Invocations of the Ethereals. Each Ethereal can only use each power once per battle round.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Revered Ethereal" id="dca1-e4ff-8de2-4745" hidden="false">
            <description>The model can invoke 1 additional invocation per turn.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Honor Guard" id="8742-2c34-16e0-43ce" hidden="false">
            <description>Ethereal Guards do not prevent an Ethereal from joining another unit. They will go with him!</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Flesh Shaper" id="33e7-d36c-e19d-429a" hidden="false">
            <description>The model and its attached unit gain "Deflagrate(6+)" for all melee attacks.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Trail Shaper" id="36b7-1f18-652b-489b" hidden="false">
            <description>After all units have been placed in the Deployment phase, you may remove and redeploy this model and its attached unit.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="War Shaper" id="69fe-6d7b-cf3c-4208" hidden="false">
            <description>The model and its attached unit automatically remove all Battleshock tokens during each Reinforcement phase.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Cadre Fireblade" id="60e0-c45d-45d9-4ece" hidden="false">
            <description>All ranged weapons of the Cadre Fireblade and its attached unit gain the "Deflagrate(6+)" ability.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Darkstrider" id="c016-905b-4db2-4c6b" hidden="false">
            <description>All Markerlights of Darkstrider and his attached unit gain +6" range. Darkstrider has the "Infiltrator" and "Vanguard" ability.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Longstrike" id="aa9e-a458-0890-4391" hidden="false">
            <description>The model must start the game inside a Hammerhead unit (even though the vehicle does not have a transport capacity!) and can't disembark until it is destroyed. The Hammerhead that is chosen improves its Ballistic Skill by +1.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Monofilament" id="2ef5-cbe9-5de7-4e92" hidden="false">
            <description>If the target enemy unit is in cover and at least one hit has been scored with the weapon, the terrain counts as difficult and dangerous terrain until the end of the next activation of the target unit.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Deployment" id="635d-d021-41c5-4d6e" hidden="false">
            <description>Support Turrets always start in reserves and arrive whenever the controlling player wants to and in whatever quantity. Do not make reserve rolls for Support Turrets. During each Reinforcement phase, one Support Turret per Breacher or Strike Team can be placed anywhere within 3" of any Breacher or Strike Team. If a Breacher or Strike team is currently transported within a Devilfish, the Support Turret can be placed within 3" of the Devilfish. Support Turrets count as being completely immobilised after setup.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Expanding the sphere of influence" id="ec5f-3def-2231-44e0" hidden="false">
            <description>If a Support Turret is placed on a mission objective that was secured by a Troop selection (via the "Objective secured!" ability), it will still control the mission objective, even if an enemy unit is standing on it. This means all Support Turrets on an objective need to be destroyed, before the enemy may capture or contest the point!</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="XV22-2 Stalker" id="29e7-5655-f740-40aa" hidden="false">
            <description>The models gains the "Infiltrator" and "Stealth" ability.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="XV85-2 Enforcer" id="2c9b-0fcf-04e0-408d" hidden="false">
            <description>The model gains a 2+ armor save. Additionally, it may select one more weapon or support system.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="XV86-2 Coldstar" id="a041-afba-293f-4b5b" hidden="false">
            <description>The models gains the "Jetbike" unit type and the "Hit & Run" ability.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="XV86-3 Supernova" id="e5fa-e1c5-03d9-4080" hidden="false">
            <description>The model gains +1 Attack and +1 Initiative.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Sniper" id="34f3-b13b-c76e-4a7e" hidden="false">
            <description>A model equipped with a Kroot long rifle improves its BS by +1.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Note" id="04c3-42e5-0de0-4552" hidden="false">
            <description>Sniper Drones in this unit are not controlled by a Drone controller and can be removed normally as casualties.</description>
        </rule>
